title: Starlink support for Ukraine will exceed $100M by end of year
summary: Starlink support for Ukraine will exceed $100 million by the end of the year, Elon Musk said earlier today. The SpaceX CEO’s response...

title: NASA to Provide Update on DART, World’s First Planetary Defense Test
summary: NASA will host a media briefing at 2 p.m. EDT, Tuesday, Oct. 11, to discuss the agency’s Double Asteroid Redirection Test (DART) mission and its intentional collision with its target asteroid, Dimorphos.

title: Eutelsat says satellite jammers within Iran are disrupting foreign channels
summary: Signals originating within Iran have been jamming two Eutelsat satellites that provide foreign broadcasts in the country since Sept. 26, the French operator said Oct. 7.

title: Rocket Lab launches Argos tracking payload
summary: A Rocket Lab Electron rocket launched a satellite Oct. 7 carrying a payload for U.S. and French government agencies that will track wildlife and collect other sensor data.

title: NASA's InSight Waits Out Dust Storm
summary: InSight’s team is taking steps to help the solar-powered lander continue operating for as long as possible.
